<?PHP
// $var, $docroot etc. are already populated by webGui/template.php before
// this page's body is evaluated - no require needed to read
// $var['csrf_token'] below (see Stacks.page for the same convention).
//
// No Markdown="false" here, on purpose - unlike Tasks-category tab
// pages elsewhere in this plugin, Settings-category pages are meant to
// be authored in Unraid's own markdown-based settings idiom (confirmed
// by reading Community Applications' own ca_settings.page on a real
// box): "_(Label)_:" as a term, ": <input>" as its definition, and
// "> hint text" as a blockquote hint below it, all inside a
// <form markdown="1">. That's what gives every native settings page
// its consistent label/input/hint layout - raw <div>/<label> soup (the
// previous version of this page) doesn't get any of that styling.
?>
<link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="<?autov('/plugins/stacksUI/css/stacksUI.css')?>">

<form id="stacksUI-settings-page-root" markdown="1" data-csrf-token="<?= htmlspecialchars($var['csrf_token'] ?? '') ?>" onsubmit="return false;">

_(Stacks directory)_:
: <input type="text" id="stacksUI-settings-dir" placeholder="/boot/config/plugins/stacksUI">

> Where each stack's docker-compose.yml/.env/meta.json live. Changing this moves any existing stacks to the new location.

_(Default data root)_:
: <input type="text" id="stacksUI-settings-dataroot" placeholder="/mnt/user/appdata">

> Used to pre-fill a DATA_ROOT suggestion in new stacks' .env - doesn't affect stacks you've already created.

_(Backup path)_ (optional):
: <input type="text" id="stacksUI-settings-backup" placeholder="e.g. /mnt/user/backups/stacksUI">

> If set, a copy of a stack's docker-compose.yml/.env/meta.json is mirrored here after every create/edit. Leave blank to disable.

_(Hide Docker tab)_:
: <select class='narrow' id="stacksUI-toggle-hideDocker">
  <option value="1">Yes</option>
  <option value="0">No</option>
  </select>

> Hides the built-in "Docker" tab, since stacks are managed from the Stacks tab instead.

_(Hide Apps tab)_:
: <select class='narrow' id="stacksUI-toggle-hideApps">
  <option value="1">Yes</option>
  <option value="0">No</option>
  </select>

> Hides Community Applications' "Apps" tab, since the Stacks App Store covers app installs instead.

_(Enable Stacks App Store tab)_:
: <select class='narrow' id="stacksUI-toggle-enableAppStore">
  <option value="1">Yes</option>
  <option value="0">No</option>
  </select>

> Shows or hides stacksUI's own "Stacks App Store" tab. These three toggles take effect immediately, but a full page reload (not just clicking between tabs) is needed to see a tab appear or disappear from the top nav bar.

<p id="stacksUI-settings-page-error" class="stacksUI-error" style="display:none"></p>

&nbsp;
: <span><input type="button" id="stacksUI-settings-page-save" value="Apply"> <span id="stacksUI-settings-page-saved" style="display:none">Saved.</span></span>

</form>

<script src="<?autov('/plugins/stacksUI/js/stacksUISettings.js')?>"></script>
